The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bharti ties up $354m loan

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Jan. 12: Bharti Tele-Ventures Ltd has tied up an international funding of $354 million to pay Ericsson and Nokia for telecom equipment required to set up networks.

 The fund has been arranged at an approximate spread of 35 basis points over the Libor. The firm has opted for the combination of long-term foreign currency loans of $254 million from Swedish export credit agency EKN with a door-to-door maturity of 10 years. The lender bank for the facility is ABN Amro and it shall be used to pay Ericsson. It has also received a $100-million loan from FinnFund with a door-to-door maturity of 10 years. It is guaranteed for payment by Finnvera and shall be used to pay Nokia. 




